            <div type="translation">
                <p>I no longer fear God, but I love Him. For love casts out fear</p> 
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>The inscription is identified with a saying of Saint Antonios from the Apophegmata Patrum (PG 65,85). The same text is proposed for the scroll of Saint Antonios in the Painter's Manual of Dionysios of Fourna (<bibl><ptr target="#DionysiusofFourna1909"/>, <citedRange>292, incipit 273</citedRange></bibl>, <bibl><ptr target="#Sacopoulo1966"/>,<citedRange> 105, n.1</citedRange></bibl>).</p> 
